# Angular Component File Structure

## Feature Components (business logic)

**Always separate files**: `.ts` + `.html` (+ `.scss` only if custom styles are needed).

```
features/persons/components/person-list/
├── person-list.component.ts    # Logic, signals, service calls
├── person-list.component.html  # Template with DaisyUI + Tailwind
└── person-list.component.scss  # ONLY if complex animations needed
```

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-person-list',
  standalone: true,
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  imports: [DataTableComponent, FilterBarComponent],
  templateUrl: './person-list.component.html',
})
```

**No empty `.scss` files** — omit `styleUrls` entirely if no custom styles.

## Shared UI Components (small, generic)

Inline `template` is allowed when the template is **under ~40 lines** and the component has no business logic:

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-stat-card',
  standalone: true,
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  imports: [LucideAngularModule],
  template: `
    <div class="stat bg-base-100 shadow-sm rounded-box">
      <div class="stat-figure text-primary">
        <i-lucide [img]="icon()" class="size-6" />
      </div>
      <div class="stat-title text-xs">{{ label() }}</div>
      <div class="stat-value text-xl">{{ value() }}</div>
    </div>
  `,
})
export class StatCardComponent {
  label = input.required<string>();
  value = input.required<string | number>();
  icon = input.required<LucideIconData>();
}
```

## Decision Criteria

| | Feature component | Shared component |
|---|---|---|
| Template size | Any | < 40 lines |
| Business logic | Yes (service calls, routing) | No (pure I/O) |
| File structure | `templateUrl` + separate `.html` | `template` inline OK |
| `.scss` file | Only if needed | Never |

## Mandatory Patterns

- `standalone: true` — always
- `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush` — always
- `input()` / `output()` — never `@Input()` / `@Output()`
- `computed()` for derived state
- `host: { class: 'block' }` when the component needs block display
